Spark Streaming 
===========
Managed  spark structured atreaming service offeref by Databricks and autoloader.
Autoloader - In Databricks is a powerfull feature designed to efficiently and incrementally load data from cloud storage into Databricks, especially when new files keep arriving continuously. It's ideal for building streaming data pipelines without manually tracking new files.

Autoloader Architecture
=================
Idempotency/exactly Once - Uploading the data to the destination which is required or only new data instead of the entire load.
As new files are detected, their metadata is saved in the scalable key-value store (RocksDB) at the checkpoint location of your AutoLoader pipeline. This helps ensure that each file is processed only once.
Checkpoint -  Is like your repository where you can just dump all your information about your stream processing everything.

Schema Inference - It says i(autoloader)  will infer the schema of your streaming query.
When autoloader reads for the first time, it infers the schema by sampling up to 50 GB or 1000 files - whichever comes first. It then saves this schems information in a _schemas folder at the specified cloudFiles.schemaLocation, so it can keep track of any schema changes over time. Autoloader checks for new column while processing your data. If it finds any, it stops the stream and throws an UnknownFieldException. But before this happens, Auto Loader peforms schema inference on the latest micro-batch (updates the cached schema)and updates the schema location by adding the new columns at the end. It keeps the data types of the existing columns umchanged.


Schema Evolution mode - Resue - if you have 100 ore columns it just creats the disc with col and value \
	                         addNewColumns - it will create 100 new columns which is not much efficient.

