DELTA SHARING
=============
Delta sharing is an open protocol developed by Databricks that allows you to securely share live data across organizations, platforms, and clouds - without needing to copy or move the data.
Think of it as a universal data-sharing standard where the provider shares data once, and multiple consumers can access it directly in real-time.

Why Delta Sharing - you can access the metstores of multiple workspaces used easily(communicate between the different workspaces/collaborate), If persons data is not on databricks then we can use deltasharing

Delta Sharing Types
====================
D2D Databricks To Databricks - Both the data of the workspaces(attached to different metastore, and we have workspaces attached to the different Metastore) are on the Databricks and they want to talk to each other.
ex- for internal or cross-organization use, if both are on Databricks.
Open Delta Sharing - for external users, via open-source Delta Sharing client.

